modules.description: This module provides functions to create, modify, and extract zip archives. It operates on file paths and directories, allowing users to zip a directory recursively, add or delete individual files in a zip archive, and extract files to a specified directory. Concrete use cases include packaging application resources into a zip file, updating specific files in an archive, and extracting assets for deployment or processing.

This module handles zip archive manipulation, supporting creation, modification, and extraction. It works with file paths and directories, enabling recursive zipping, file addition or deletion, and targeted extraction. Users can package directories into zip files, update specific files within archives, or extract content for deployment and processing. Example tasks include bundling application assets, modifying configuration files inside a zip, or extracting resources for runtime use.
